<p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>OpenMPI version: 1.4.3<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Platform: IBM P5, 32 processors, 256 GB memory, Symmetric
Multi-Threading (SMT) enabled<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Application: starts up 48 processes and does MPI using
MPI_Barrier, MPI_Get, MPI_Put (lots of transfers, large amounts of data)<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Issue:&nbsp; When implemented using Open MPI vs. IBM&#8217;s MPI
(&#8216;poe&#8217; from HPC Toolkit), the application runs 3-5 times slower.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>I suspect that IBM&#8217;s MPI implementation must take advantage
of some knowledge that it has about data transfers that Open MPI is not taking
advantage of.<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Any suggestions?<o:p></o:p></p>

